[{"id":"VH906880","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH906871.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The system is moving and accelerating upward. A pair of scissors cuts the rope. Which of the following describes the motion of the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 kilogram\"><math alttext=\"10 kilogram\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mn>10</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> block immediately after the rope has been cut?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH906880_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two blocks in a vertical arrangement connected by a vertical rope. The upper block has a mass of 5 kilograms, and the lower block has a mass of 10 kilograms. An upward applied force of magnitude F acts on the upper block.\" height=\"217\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH906871.g01.png\" width=\"180\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\">Two blocks are connected by a rope, as shown above. The masses of the blocks are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 kilograms\"><math alttext=\"5 kilograms\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mn>5</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> for the upper block and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 kilograms\"><math alttext=\"10 kilograms\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mn>10</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> for the lower block. An upward applied force of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"italic\"><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> acts on the upper block.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The block continues to move upward and to accelerate upward.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The block begins to move downward but continues to accelerate upward.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The block continues to move upward but begins to accelerate downward.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The block begins to move downward and to accelerate downward.</p>"],"answer":2}]